name: 4179 Toutatis
description: Provisional designation 1989 AC, is an elongated, stony asteroid and slow rotator, classified as near-Earth object and potentially hazardous asteroid of the Apollo and Alinda group, approximately 2.5 kilometers in diameter. Discovered by French astronomer Christian Pollas at Caussols in 1989, the asteroid was named after Toutatis from Celtic mythology.

name: 1996 HW1
description: Asteroid (8567) 1996 HW1 - hereafter referred to as HW1 - was discovered on 23 April 1996 by T. Gehrels as part of the Spacewatch survey at Steward Observatory. HW1 is in the Amor class of near-Earth asteroids (NEAs) with a semimajor axis a = 2.046 AU and perihelion distance q = 1.128 AU.
